      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done. Aggregation behavior changed as follows:\n\nBefore:\n  TotalMemorySizeMiB is written only when ALL endpoints succeed\n  (endpointsFound \u0026\u0026 allSuccess). A single EBADR/io_error hides the\n  whole property.\n\nAfter:\n  TotalMemorySizeMiB is written when AT LEAST ONE endpoint is\n  successfully aggregated. Endpoints returning EBADR or io_error are\n  logged at debug level and skipped; any other D-Bus error sets\n  hasError and results in messages::internalError.\n\nImplementation:\n  1. Removed allSuccess entirely.\n  2. Moved acc-\u003eendpointsFound \u003d true from the association callback\n     into the success path of afterGetMemorySize.\n  3. Destructor condition reduced to `if (endpointsFound)`.\n\nSee PS10:\n  - gate:            https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/88035/10/redfish-core/lib/processor.hpp#836\n  - endpointsFound:  https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/88035/10/redfish-core/lib/processor.hpp#875",
      "parentUuid": "a0c996c6_17ec638f",
      "revId": "e5deff33afd29f774672ffcfabe589e1ba3ef314",
